!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

certificate /səˈtɪfɪkɪt/

(certificates) 

1. N-COUNT A certificate is an official document stating that particular facts are true. 证明书 

例： ...birth certificates. …出生证明。 

2. N-COUNT A certificate is an official document that you receive when you have completed a course of study or training. The qualification that you receive is sometimes also called a certificate . 结业证书 

例： To the right of the fireplace are various framed certificates. 火炉右侧是各式各样加框的证书。

</div>

